{
  "_notes": [
    "Dropdown catalog for the session selectors. Drives the cascading Track and Car pickers on BOTH the web dashboard and the Flutter app.",
    "TRACKS: a list of venues. Each venue has a 'region' (metadata, for grouping/sorting) and a 'layouts' list. Each layout string is exactly what gets stored as the session/reference key, so keep these stable once you start saving references. Cascade is venue -> layout.",
    "CARS: a list of categories. Each category has 'manufacturers' grouped by 'country', each with a 'cars' list. Cascade is category -> country -> car. The car string is stored as-is.",
    "GT7 note: 'Night' on Tokyo Expressway is a time-of-day setting, not a separate layout. 'Reverse' variants ARE separate layouts. Any key beginning with underscore is ignored by the loader.",
    "AUTO-GENERATED by gt7_catalog_scraper.py from the gt7info dataset (auto-updates with the game). Re-run after a GT7 update to refresh. Category labels and track regions are controlled by editable maps at the top of the script.",
    "AFTER EDITING: copy this file to BOTH app/static/catalog.json and flutter/assets/catalog.json so the two surfaces stay identical."
  ],
